FL,408,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1772204159
OL,3,CMet Police officer who stole #2.25
OL,4,Ctuna baguette 'would have been sacked'
OL,6,FAccording to a written misconduct
OL,7,Fruling, Mr Fyfe spent "some moments
OL,8,Flooking at the sandwich fridge" before
OL,9,Fselecting the item and "immediately
OL,10,Fwalked out of the store without making
OL,11,Fany attempt to pay for it".
OL,13,FA Pret employee witnessed him leaving
OL,14,Fthe shop holding the baguette, getting
OL,15,Finto the passenger seat of a police
OL,16,Fcar and driving off.
OL,18,FShe later reported the incident to
OL,19,Fanother officer who had come into the
OL,20,Fstore to buy a coffee, the ruling said.
OL,26,@oD@WOUpD@_O]qD@XOUsD@ZO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/4
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,408,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1772204159
OL,3,CMet Police officer who stole #2.25
OL,4,Ctuna baguette 'would have been sacked'
OL,6,FOn May 1 2025, Mr Fyfe was interviewed
OL,7,Funder caution when he admitted taking
OL,8,Fthe item but denied stealing it and
OL,9,Fsaid his failure to pay was an
OL,10,F"oversight" because of lack of sleep
OL,11,Fand a recent argument in what he
OL,12,Fdescribed as a "brain fart".
OL,14,FFollowing a hearing held on February
OL,15,F13, a panel found his behaviour
OL,16,Famounted to gross misconduct and would
OL,17,Fhave justified his dismissal had he
OL,18,Fstill been a member of the force.
OL,26,@rD@AOUrD@KO]tD@POUtD@[O]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/4
